Key to Success - Motivation 
Motivation is an important factor of success. Sometimes it's easy, sometimes it's not. Here's a few 
comments and tips on the subject of motivation. 
 
7 Keys to Create a Customer Focused Culture 
Conventional approaches to motivate workers and enhance customer satisfaction through mission 
statements have often fallen short. What's needed is a new approach to create a customer-focused culture 
where employees want to contribute. 
 
Building Bridges of Communication 
Building a 'bridge of understanding' between parties is fundamental if your business communication is to 
succeed. 
 
Great Communicators and the Unspoken Secret 
Studies have shown that it is the great listeners who get the raises, promotions, and perks in life, not 
necessarily the great talkers. 
 
Re-Discovering Your Career Passion 
If you've been feeling resigned or cynical in your work-attitude, it is time to take responsibility and take 
action NOW. Leverage the resources that are available to you, and commit to improving your career 
situation. 
 
Leadership - Do We Know What it is? 4 Pointers to Start You on the Road to Becoming a Leader 
It might be reasonable to assume that leadership can be developed. However, there has been and still is, 
considerable debate on the issue. Even the experts are divided. This article shows how everyone, 
irrespective of their position, can develop lead 
 
Thoughts on Empowerment 
Empowerment is an overused term and underused practice. This short article gives you ideas for putting 
empowerment into practice. 
 
5 Tips for Finding Your Core Competencies 
We know what training is, but do we understand why training fails? 
